---
description: Do not use Unicode en dash or em dash in this repo (use hyphen or punctuation).
alwaysApply: true
---

# No en/em dashes

Never type U+2013 (en dash) or U+2014 (em dash) in user-facing strings, comments, migrations, markdown, or code.

Use instead:

- A normal hyphen `-` for ranges (e.g. `300-900`, `Mon-Fri`, `1-4`).
- A comma, semicolon, period, colon, or rephrasing instead of sentence-level em-dash breaks.

Running `npm run lint` fails if either character appears under `src/`, `supabase/`, `.cursor/rules/`, or root markdown/config files scanned by `scripts/check-no-en-em-dash.mjs`.
